Parliament, Wednesday 4 April 2018 - The Speakers’ Forum will meet for a two-day programme in Pretoria tomorrow (Thursday) and Friday, 6 April to discuss, among other matters, Ethics Governance in the Public Sector, budgeting process and review of the allocation of seats in the Provincial Legislatures. Other discussions to take centre-stage at the meeting are the proposal on processing the High Level Panel Report recommendations, the South African Legislative Sector Bill and collective bargaining for the SA Legislative Sector. Members of the Forum are the Speaker and Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly, the Chairperson and Deputy Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces and the Speakers and Deputy Speakers of all nine Provincial Legislatures. Parliament’s National Assembly Speaker, Ms Baleka Mbete, chairs the Forum, a decision-making body which oversees management and coordination of legislative sector programmes. There will be a launch of the South African Legislative Sector-European Union (SALS-EU) Programme at the end of the Speakers’ Forum meeting on Thursday 5 April 2018. The launch is open to the Media. Members of the media who wish to cover the launch of the SALS-EU Programme should RSVP Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 or at mmpindi@parliament.gov.za CC: mdlula@parliament.gov.za NB: The Speakers’ Forum meeting is a closed session but there will be a media briefing at the end of day one (Thursday, 5 March). The venue is the Sheraton Hotel, Pretoria. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ON BEHALF OF THE SPEAKERS’ FORUM OF THE LEGISLATIVE SECTOR OF SOUTH AFRICA
